definition.value: A member of the class of  dibenzofurans that is  dibenzo[b,d]furan substituted by a chloro group at position 7 and a hydroxy group at position 2.
A member of the class of dibenzofurans that is dibenzo[b,d]furan substituted by a chloro group at position 8 and hydroxy groups at position 2 and 7.
A member of the class of dibenzofurans that is dibenzo[b,d]furan substituted by chloro groups at positions 2 and 8 and a hydroxy group at position 3.
A member of the class of dibenzofurans that is dibenzo[b,d]furan substituted by a hydroxy group at position 3 and chloro groups at positions 2, 4, 7, 8 and 9 respectively.
A member of the class of dibenzofurans that is dibenzo[b,d]furan substituted by a hydroxy group at position 3 and chloro groups at positions 6 and 7 respectively.
A member of the class of dibenzofurans that is dibenzo[b,d]furan substituted by a hydroxy group at position 1 and chloro groups at positions 6 and 7.
A member of the class of dibenzofurans that is dibenzo[b,d]furan substituted by a hydroxy group at position 1 and chloro groups at positions 4 and 8 respectively.
A member of the class of  hydroxybiphenyls that is biphenyl-4-ol substituted by chloro groups at positions 2', 3, 5 and 5' respectively.
A monocarboxylic acid that is cyclopropanecarboxylic acid substituted by methyl groups at positions 1 and 2 and a 3,5-dichlorophenylcarbamoyl group at position 2.
A member of the class of ureas that is  1-methylurea substituted by a hydroxy group at position 1 and a 3,4-dichlorophenyl group at position 3.
A member of the class of caprolactams resulting from the Beckmann rearrangement of the oxime derivative of cholest-4-en-3-one.
An  androstanoid that is 5alpha-androstane substituted by a methyl group at position 4, a hydroxy group at position 17 and an oxo group at position 3.
A steroid ester that is androst-4-en-17beta-yl propanoate substituted by an oxo group at position 3 and a fluoro group at position 17.
A 16alpha-hydroxy steroid that is  estriol in which the hydroxy group at position 3 is replaced by an allyloxy group.
A steroid ester that is pregn-4-en-21-yl acetate substituted by oxo groups at positions 3 and 20, hydroxy groups at positions 11 and 17 and a fluoro group at position 6.
A 3-oxo steroid that is estr-5(10)-ene substituted by an oxo group at position 3 and a beta-hydroxy group at position 17.
A 3-oxo Delta(4)-steroid that is estr-4-ene substituted by a beta-hydroxy group at position 17 and an alpha-methyl group at position 2.
A 3-oxo Delta(4)-steroid that is estr-4-ene substituted by an oxo group at position 3, methyl groups at positions 2 and 17 and a beta-hydroxy group at position 17.
A C21-steroid that is 5beta-pregn-11-ene substituted by oxo groups at positions 3 and 20.
A 3-hydroxy steroid that is estra-1,3,5(10)-triene substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 3 and 16.
A 16beta-hydroxy steroid that is estra-1,3,5(10)-trien-16beta-ol substituted by a methoxy group at position 3.
A 2-oxo steroid that is a derivative of pregnane obtained by the loss of a methylene group.
A steroid ester that is 5alpha-androstane substituted by an acetoxy group at position 17.
A 3-oxo Delta(4)-steroid that is  progesterone substituted by a beta-methyl group at position 16.
A steroid ester that is methyl (17E)-pregna-4,17-dien-21-oate substituted by oxo groups at positions 3 and 11.
An organosulfonate salt obtained by reaction of pentamidine with two equivalents of 2-hydroxyethylsulfonic acid.
An epoxide that is oxirane substituted by a phenyl group at position 3 and a 4-nitrophenyl group at position 2 (the trans-isomer).
A steroid ester that is pregn-4-en-21-yl acetate substituted by a fluoro group at position 9, hydroxy groups at positions 11 and 17 and oxo groups at positions 3 and 20 respectively.
The hydrochloride salt of cycloguanil.
A fluorinated steroid that is pregn-4-ene substituted by a fluoro group at position 2, a methyl group at position 2 and oxo groups at positions 3, 11 and 20.
A steroid ester that is 5beta-pregnane substituted by an oxo group at position 20 and acetoxy groups at positions 3 and 12.
An  androstanoid that is (5alpha)-androst-1-en-17beta-yl propanoate substituted by an oxo group at position 3.
A triterpenoid that is (18alpha)-19,28-epoxyoleanane substituted by a hydroxy group at position 3.
A steroid ester that is pregn-4-en-21-yl acetate substituted by oxo group at positions 3 and 20, a methyl group at position 6 and hydroxy groups at positions 11 and 17 respectively.
An  androstanoid that is androst-4-ene substituted by an alpha-fluoro group at position 2 and a beta-hydroxy group at position 17.
